      • getIndicesComparator

        public java.util.Comparator<int[]> getIndicesComparator()
        Description copied from class: JointDomainIndexer
        Returns a comparator that orders indices arrays.

        If JointDomainIndexer.supportsJointIndexing(), this is guaranteed to produce the same order as the natural order of the corresponding joint indexes. If not JointDomainIndexer.isDirected() or JointDomainIndexer.hasCanonicalDomainOrder(), then the comparator implements a reverse lexicographical ordering (see Comparators.reverseLexicalIntArray()).

        The comparator is intended to be used with arrays of length DomainList.size().

        Overrides:
        getIndicesComparator in class JointDomainIndexer

      • supportsJointIndexing

        public boolean supportsJointIndexing()
        Description copied from class: JointDomainIndexer
        Indicates whether class supports operations involving single integer jointIndex representation. This will be false when the joint cardinality of the component domains is larger than 231.
        Specified by:
        supportsJointIndexing in class JointDomainIndexer

      • supportsOutputIndexing

        public boolean supportsOutputIndexing()
        Description copied from class: JointDomainIndexer
        Indicates whether class supports operations involving single integer output index representation of the subset of domains identified by JointDomainIndexer.getOutputSet(). This will be false when the joint cardinality of the component output domains is larger than 231. Note that this can be true when JointDomainIndexer.supportsJointIndexing() is false.
        Specified by:
        supportsOutputIndexing in class JointDomainIndexer

      • getCardinality

        public int getCardinality()
        Description copied from class: JointDomainIndexer

      • getOutputCardinality

        public int getOutputCardinality()
        Description copied from class: JointDomainIndexer
        The number of possible combinations of output domain elements. Equal to the product of all of the output domain sizes. Will be the same as JointDomainIndexer.getCardinality() if not JointDomainIndexer.isDirected().

      • getStride

        public int getStride(int i)
        Description copied from class: JointDomainIndexer
        Returns amount by which joint index returned by JointDomainIndexer.jointIndexFromIndices(int...) changes when ith element index changes by 1.

        This can be used to iterate over the joint indexes for one dimension for fixed values of all of the other dimensions.

      • undirectedJointIndexToElementIndex

        public int undirectedJointIndexToElementIndex(int jointIndex,
                                     int domainIndex)
        Description copied from class: JointDomainIndexer
        Computes element index for a single domain from a joint index using undirected ordering of domains.

        This is like JointDomainIndexer.undirectedJointIndexToIndices(int, int[]) but only computes one element index.

        Specified by:
        undirectedJointIndexToElementIndex in class JointDomainIndexer
        Parameters:
        jointIndex - must be in range [0, JointDomainIndexer.getCardinality()-1].
        domainIndex - must be in range [0, DomainList.size()-1].

        See Also:
        JointDomainIndexer.jointIndexToElementIndex(int, int)
